# Update test/dune to include new test modules; add bisect_ppx to clawq.opam test deps

## Requirements

- As new test files are created by other M6 tasks, update the `(modules ...)` stanza in `test/dune` to include each new module: `test_helpers`, `test_pairing`, `test_memory`, `test_tools`, `test_provider`, `test_channel_formats`, `test_contracts`, `test_commands`.
- Add each new module to the `test_main.ml` `Alcotest.run` call with the appropriate suite name and suite value.
- In `clawq.opam`, add `"bisect_ppx" {with-test}` to the `depends` section so CI installs it when running tests.
- This task is essentially a coordination task: whenever a new test file is merged, this file must be updated. The acceptance criteria track the final state after all M6 test files exist.

## Implementation Notes

The current `test/dune` likely has a `(modules (...))` stanza listing all test module names. Add new entries alphabetically. The `(libraries ...)` stanza may need `sqlite3` if `test_helpers.ml` uses it directly (it does, via `Memory.init`). Check `test/dune` to see current library list. `bisect_ppx` in the opam file uses `{with-test}` flag so it's only installed in test environments.

## Acceptance Criteria

Done when:
- `dune build test/test_main.exe` succeeds with all new test modules included.
- `dune runtest` runs all new suites (they appear in the test output).
- `opam install . --deps-only --with-test` installs `bisect_ppx`.
- `make test` passes.
